Proposed Solution
High-level solution
The solution takes the AS-IS CSV topology as input and produces a TARGET CSV topology with the same schema, but with optimized content.
It works in six major stages:
Refined extraction
Parses the raw dataset into producer-consumer flow objects, including routing evidence, queue roles, ambiguity, and topology health.
Topology and complexity analysis
Builds queue-manager graph structures and measures flow-level and node-level complexity, including hop count, hotspots, routing-only QMs, broken flows, and orphan flows.
Optimization decision engine
Applies rule-based and topology-aware decisions to determine how each flow should be handled in target state:
preserve conceptually
canonicalize
split local-to-remote
simplify routing
exclude invalid flows
flag manual review where needed
Optional expert override layer
Allows controlled human-in-the-loop refinement for ambiguous or high-risk cases without breaking the automated pipeline.
Target topology generation
Produces a clean, canonical target flow model with one QM per app, deterministic routing, standard queue/channel naming, and target-state MQ objects.
Validation, comparison, and export
Validates target flows against constraints, compares AS-IS vs TARGET complexity, generates explanation reports, and exports the final target CSV in the original schema layout.
How it addresses the problem
It addresses the problem by:
reducing routing complexity
enforcing one QM per application
removing invalid and ambiguous topology from target design
generating deterministic QM-to-QM routing
preserving explainability for every transformation decision
making the output suitable for automation and enterprise review
