Limitations and Future Work
Current limitations
1. Ambiguous ownership may still require expert confirmation
When an application appears across multiple AS-IS QMs, the pipeline can assign canonical target ownership, but expert review may still be needed for final enterprise approval.
2. Some invalid flows are excluded rather than “repaired”
For orphan or broken flows, the solution avoids speculative fixes unless there is sufficient evidence. This is correct and safe, but it means some legacy issues remain unresolved outside target generation.
3. Hotspot handling is signal-based, not a full balancing optimizer
The solution detects fan-in / fan-out hotspots and uses them as optimization signals, but does not yet perform a full post-target balancing redesign.
